	abstract = {Hot-film measurements in a fully developed channel flow have been made in an attempt to gain more insight into the process of Reynolds stress production. The background for this effort is the observation of a certain sequence of events (deceleration, ejection and sweep) in the wall region of turbulent flows by Corino (1965) and Corino \& Brodkey (1969). The instantaneous product signal
